results.name: Decimal expansion of 1 - 2^(-1/3).
comment: Blomer shows that there are x/log^k x powerful numbers up to x, where k = 0.20629947... is this constant.
link: Valentin Blomer, Binary quadratic forms with large discriminants and sums of two squareful numbers II, Journal of the London Mathematical Society 71:1 (2005), pp. 69-84.
